	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's not as direct an issue as straight up brightness.
<br />
<br />Taking the art we use on the console, and throwing it up on a PC tends to be more subdued, less saturated, and a little lighter at the normal video settings.
<br />
<br />On the consoles, the low end drops off quicker, and colors are generally a bit brighter and more saturated. The DAC's respond a bit differently as well.
<br />
<br />GC's tend to be a bit more colorful, whereas the ps2 seems to run it's white level really hot.
<br />
<br />I believe the issue is related to PC's generally being set up for a gamma of 1 (linear RGB), whereas the TV's have a slightly lower one.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


