	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />PCs are set up to approximate sRGB, which uses gamma=2.2. The higher black level of TV (7.5%) may be mimicking a higher gamma of 2.5. (I just checked in a graphing calculator program, and the curve for g=2.2 black=7.5% resembles that for g=2.5 black=0.) The Game Boy Advance also seems to have a ridiculously high black level (25%) that wasn't taken into account on launch titles.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
